---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
    title="Render Performance Demos"
    description="Interactive CSS render performance demos for layout, paint, and compositing."
>
    <section class="site-hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Tool</p>

        <h1>
            Render performance demos
        </h1>

        <p class="intro">
            Good CSS architecture helps reduce layout, paint, and compositing
            costs before they become production problems.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Animation cost comparison
        </h2>

        <form class="tool-panel" data-render-demo>
            <label for="animation-mode">
                Animation mode
            </label>

            <select id="animation-mode" class="tool-input" data-animation-mode>
                <option value="transform">transform</option>
                <option value="width">width</option>
            </select>
        </form>

        <div class="render-demo-stage">
            <div class="render-demo-box" data-render-demo-box></div>
        </div>

        <p data-render-output>
            transform usually avoids layout recalculation and is often safer for movement.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Avoid vs prefer
        </h2>

        <div class="performance-grid">
            <article class="performance-card performance-card--bad">
                <h3>
                    Avoid
                </h3>

<pre><code>.panel {
    transition: width 0.3s ease;
}</code></pre>
            </article>

            <article class="performance-card performance-card--good">
                <h3>
                    Prefer
                </h3>

<pre><code>.panel {
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
}</code></pre>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Rendering containment
        </h2>

<pre><code>.component-list {
    content-visibility: auto;
    contain-intrinsic-size: 0 40rem;
}

.widget {
    contain: layout paint;
}</code></pre>

        <p>
            Containment can reduce the impact of complex isolated sections, but
            it should be used deliberately and tested carefully.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Architecture guidance
        </h2>

        <ul>
            <li>prefer transform and opacity for frequent animation</li>
            <li>avoid animating layout-heavy properties unless necessary</li>
            <li>contain expensive isolated widgets where appropriate</li>
            <li>test reduced motion support</li>
            <li>avoid global CSS patterns that trigger broad visual changes</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <script type="module" src="/scripts/render-performance-demos.js"></script>
</DocsLayout>
